## Load libraries
```{r}

# psych is needed for ICC function
#readxl reads in .xlsx files

# you will need to use install.packages for these libraries if you have not done so previously. library is used to load the packages once they are already installed.

library("psych")
library("readxl")
library("dplyr")
library("irr")

```

### Forest plot to view ICCs per group and session
```{r}

library(forestplot)

icc_data <- data.frame(
  Category = c("Session 1 TBI", "Session 1 HC", "Session 2 TBI", "Session 2 HC"),
  ICC_Value = c(0.59, 0.30, 0.70, 0.69),
  Lower_Bound = c(0.37, 0.01, 0.51, 0.51),
  Upper_Bound = c(0.75, 0.37, 0.82, 0.82)
)

#customize x axis tick sizes
own <- fpTxtGp()
own # see all parameters
own$ticks$cex <- 1 #tick labels
own <- fpTxtGp(label = gpar(fontfamily = "Arial"),ticks = gpar(cex=1))

#Create custom style. HCs are in blue and TBI in black
styles <- fpShapesGp(
  lines = list(
    gpar(col = "black"),
    gpar(col = "blue"),
    gpar(col = "black"),
    gpar(col = "blue")
  ), 
  box = list(
    gpar(col = "black"),
    gpar(col = "blue"),
    gpar(col = "black"),
    gpar(col = "blue")
  )
)        

# Create a forest plot
forestplot(
  labeltext = icc_data$Category,
  vertices = TRUE,
  mean = icc_data$ICC_Value,
  lower = icc_data$Lower_Bound,
  upper = icc_data$Upper_Bound,
  xlog = FALSE,  # Set to TRUE for a log-scale plot
  title = "ICCs",
  clip = c(0, 1),  # Set the range of the x-axis
  xticks = c(0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0),  # Customize x-axis ticks as needed
  #col = fpColors(box = "royalblue", lines = "black"),
  shapes_gp = styles,
  zero = 0.0,  # Set the position of the zero line
  boxsize = .07,  # Adjust the size of boxes
  textsize = c(10,8),
  axes = gpar(cex = 2),
  txt_gp =own, 
  grid = structure(c((.80)),
                  gp = gpar(lty = 2, col = "#CCCCFF")),
  xfactor = 2
)
```
